<A>__{jack is wearing a knapsack. he's crossing a meadow and making his way towards a ruined hamlet. his manner is dark, purposeful, alert. the grass is long and the trees offer deep shade. jack stops. everywhere there is a profusion of wild flowers. his guardedness begins to evaporate. he has never seen anything so beautiful or utterly uncorrupted. he looks around, transfixed by delicate yellows and mauves, brash whites, harsh and brilliant crimsons, exquisite blues. the air is humming with insects, bees and butterflies. jack is transfixed.}
